@model HRHelper.Models.JobPosition

<div class="learning-material-container py-3">
    <h3 class="fw-bold mb-4" style="letter-spacing: -1px;">Recruitment Strategy: Sourcing & Metrics</h3>
    <p class="lead text-muted mb-5">
        Modern recruiting is more than just reading CVs; it's about building a sustainable pipeline, tracking efficiency, and maintaining ethical standards throughout the candidate journey.
    </p>

    <hr class="my-5 opacity-25">

    <div class="mb-5">
        <h5 class="text-danger fw-bold mb-3">1. Finding Talent: Sourcing Channels</h5>
        <p class="mb-3">A recruiter's success depends on knowing where to find the right people.</p>
        <div class="bg-light p-4 rounded-4 border-start border-danger border-5 shadow-sm">
            <p class="mb-0">A <strong>Sourcing Channel</strong> is any method or platform used to find candidates (e.g., LinkedIn, job boards, social media, or employee referrals). <strong>Sourcing candidates</strong> is typically the very <strong>first step</strong> in any professional recruitment pipeline.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-5">
        <h5 class="text-danger fw-bold mb-3">2. Legal & Ethical Compliance</h5>
        <p class="mb-3">Interviews must focus strictly on professional merit to avoid legal risks and bias.</p>
        <div class="alert alert-danger border-0 rounded-4 shadow-sm d-flex align-items-center">
            <i class="bi bi-exclamation-octagon-fill me-3 fs-4"></i>
            <div>
                <strong>Warning:</strong> In many jurisdictions, asking about a candidate's <strong>marital status</strong> (or family plans, religion, etc.) is <strong>illegal</strong> during a job interview. Stick to skills and professional experience.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-5">
        <h5 class="text-danger fw-bold mb-3">3. Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)</h5>
        <p class="mb-3">How do we measure the speed of our recruitment process?</p>
        <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm rounded-4 overflow-hidden">
            <div class="card-body p-4 bg-dark text-white">
                <h6 class="text-danger fw-bold text-uppercase small mb-2">Time-to-Hire</h6>
                <p class="mb-0">This metric measures the efficiency of the hiring process by counting the <strong>number of days from when a job is posted until a candidate accepts the offer</strong>.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-5">
        <h5 class="text-danger fw-bold mb-3">4. The Value of Passive Candidates</h5>
        <p class="mb-3">The best talent isn't always looking for a new job.</p>
        <div class="p-4 border rounded-4 bg-white shadow-sm">
            <p class="mb-0">A <strong>Passive Candidate</strong> is an individual who is <strong>not actively looking</strong> for a new job but is open to hearing about a great opportunity. Recruiting passive candidates often requires more personalized outreach and "selling" the company vision.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-5">
        <h5 class="text-danger fw-bold mb-3">5. The Recruitment Funnel</h5>
        <p class="mb-3">Recruitment is like a sales funnel; we need to see where we lose people.</p>
        <div class="p-3 bg-light rounded-4 border">
            <p class="mb-0">To track how many candidates progress from one stage of the interview process to the next, we use the <strong>Funnel Conversion Rate</strong>. This helps identify "bottlenecks" (e.g., too many people failing the technical test or dropping out after the first call).</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>